==Demographics==
{{US Census population
|2020= 1441
|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name="DecennialCensus">{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2016}}</ref>
}}As of the 2020 census, there were 1,441 people, 624 housing units, and 513 families in the CDP. The racial makeup was 92.3% [[White Americans|White]], 2.2% [[African Americans|African American]], 0.7% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.7% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.9% from some other race, and 2.9% from two or more races.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US4755820 |access-date=June 15, 2023 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry was 14.4% [[English Americans|English]], 10.6% [[German Americans|German]], 5.1% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], and 3.0% [[Welsh Americans|Welsh]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 45.1 years old. 18.6% of the population was 65 or older, with 14.8% between the ages of 65 and 74, and 3.7% was 75 or older. 17.7% of the population were under 18, with 6.0% under 5, and 11.6% was 5 or older.<ref name=":0" />

The median household income was $65,739. 5.4% of the population was in poverty, with 7.0% of people under 18, 4.6% of people between 18 and 64, and 6.3% of people over 65 were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

